{"lemma":"زَمّار","slug":"زَمّار","root":"ز.م.ر","root_slug":"ز-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-م-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18104"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18104","headword_ar":"زَمَّارٌ","root":"zmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAmirN","text_ar":"زَامِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, K,) but the latter is rare, (K,) or scarcely ever used, (S,) or it is not allowable, (Msb,) applied to a man; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAmirapu","text_ar":"زَامِرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zam~aArapN","text_ar":"زَمَّارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) applied to a woman; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"player upon a reed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who blows in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mizomaAr","text_ar":"مِزْمَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * A, Msb. *) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zam~aArapN","text_ar":"زَمَّارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fornicatress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adulteress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, A'Obeyd, Az, S, K:) so in a trad., in which it is said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaY Eano kasobi Alz~am~aArapi","text_ar":"نَهَى عَنْ كَسْبِ الزَّمَّارَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prohibited the gain of the fornicatress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, A'Obeyd, Az, S:) so called because she publishes her business: (Th:) some say that the correct word is here"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ram~aAzap","text_ar":"رَمَّازَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", because such a woman makes signs with her lips and her eyes and her eyebrows: Az says that he holds the former to be the right; and Abu-l- 'Abbás Ahmad says that the latter is wrong, and that the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beautiful prostitute:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az adds that the trad. may mean as above, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prohibited the gain of the female singer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as AHát relates on the authority of As. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["As","S","A","Msb","K","Th"]}]}}